  <article class="container-prose prose-editorial cs-body" set:html={`<h3><b>Educational Case Study Disclosure</b></h3><p>This case study is hypothetical and for educational purposes only. Scenarios, borrower profiles, loan terms, interest rates, and outcomes are illustrative examples and do not represent current offers or guaranteed terms.</p><p>For specific details including down payment requirements, closing cost estimates, interest rate details, closing cost breakdowns, payment calculations, cash-to-close estimates, or an official Loan Estimate, it is highly recommended you<a href="https://stairwaymortgage.com/schedule-call/"> schedule a meeting with one of our licensed mortgage advisors</a>.</p><p><b>Learn more:</b></p><ul><li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1"><a href="https://www.consumerfinance.gov/rules-policy/regulations/1026/24/">HomeStyle renovation loan Reg Z advertising requirements (§1026.24)</a> – CFPB official regulation</li><li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1"><a href="https://www.ecfr.gov/current/title-12/chapter-X/part-1026">HomeStyle renovation loan Reg Z full text and compliance</a> – Electronic Code of Federal Regulations</li><li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1"><a href="https://www.consumerfinance.gov/rules-policy/regulations/1026/interp-24/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Official HomeStyle renovation loan advertising interpretations (§1026.24)</a> – CFPB interpretations</li><li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1"><a href="https://www.ecfr.gov/current/title-12/chapter-X/part-1014" target="_blank" rel="noopener">HomeStyle renovation loan MAP Rule (Reg N) mortgage advertising</a> – Mortgage advertising rules</li><li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1"><a href="https://www.nmlsconsumeraccess.org/">NMLS Consumer Access – Verify HomeStyle renovation loan lender licensure</a></li></ul><p>Actual loan terms vary by credit profile, property, occupancy, location, market conditions, and lender guidelines. For current options tailored to you,<a href="https://stairwaymortgage.com/schedule-call/"> schedule a consultation</a> or<a href="https://stairwaymortgage.com/same-day-approval/"> apply online</a>.</p><p>Ready to explore your options?<a href="https://stairwaymortgage.com/schedule-call/"> Schedule a call</a> with a loan advisor.</p>		
					<h2>See How a HomeStyle Renovation Loan Made Dream Home Upgrades Possible with Single-Close Convenience
</h2>				
		<p>Amanda C., a 34-year-old interior designer in Charlotte, North Carolina, had found her dream home—a charming 1980s ranch-style house in an established neighborhood with excellent schools and mature landscaping. The home had incredible bones and sat on a beautiful lot, but it needed comprehensive updating to match Amanda's vision and her family's needs: complete kitchen renovation with modern appliances and layout, master bathroom expansion, updated flooring throughout, new HVAC system, fresh paint inside and out, and modernized lighting fixtures. Amanda and her husband earned strong combined income and had saved appropriate funds for a down payment, but purchasing the home and funding the extensive renovations separately would stretch their finances uncomfortably.</p><p>Amanda understood home renovation intimately through her design career—she knew exactly what improvements would transform this dated property into a modern, functional family home that would serve them for decades while building substantial equity. This wasn't just about aesthetics; this was about creating a home that would be the foundation for raising their two young children, building wealth through strategic homeownership, and establishing roots in a community where they could thrive long-term. But the financing puzzle seemed impossible: she needed to purchase the property and complete the renovations, ideally through a single streamlined process rather than juggling multiple loans with different rates, terms, and closing costs.</p><p>Facing similar challenges?<a href="https://stairwaymortgage.com/schedule-call/"> Schedule a call</a> to explore your options.</p><h2><b>The Challenge: Why Couldn't Amanda Finance Purchase and Renovation Together?</b></h2><p>Amanda and her husband approached three traditional mortgage lenders, explaining their situation: they wanted to purchase this specific property and complete comprehensive renovations to make it move-in ready for their family. Every lender offered the same limited solution: they could finance the home purchase in its current condition, but Amanda would need to fund the extensive renovations through separate financing—either personal loans, home equity lines of credit after closing, or out-of-pocket savings.</p><h3><b>How Do Traditional Primary Residence Mortgages Handle Major Renovation Costs?</b></h3><p>Traditional primary residence mortgages lend based on the property's current value and condition at the time of purchase. Lenders appraise the home in its existing dated state and offer financing for that appraised value. If homeowners want to renovate after purchase, they typically need to secure separate financing through personal loans, credit cards, or home equity products—each carrying their own rates, terms, fees, and approval processes.</p><h3><b>Why Was Separate Renovation Financing Problematic for Amanda?</b></h3><p>"We had saved for the down payment and closing costs, but using those funds for renovations would mean we couldn't purchase the house at all," Amanda explained. "Home equity loans weren't available yet because we didn't own the property. Personal loans for the renovation scope we needed had unfavorable terms that would significantly increase our total housing costs. And contractor financing options were expensive and inflexible. We needed a way to finance both the purchase and the complete renovation in one seamless transaction."</p><h3><b>What Home Vision Was Amanda Unable to Execute?</b></h3><p>Amanda's professional expertise as an interior designer gave her a clear vision for the property's potential. She could see past the dated finishes to the beautiful, functional family home hiding underneath. The renovations she planned weren't superficial—they were strategic improvements that would modernize critical systems, improve energy efficiency, enhance livability for her growing family, and significantly increase the home's value. This wasn't just about making the house pretty; it was about creating a smart investment that would serve as the foundation for building long-term family wealth through homeownership.</p><p>Without a HomeStyle renovation loan solution, Amanda faced disappointing compromises: purchase a different turnkey home that cost significantly more and offered less long-term value, delay their home purchase while saving additional capital for renovations, or buy the dated property and live in it for years before having funds to renovate—forcing her family to endure a home that didn't meet their needs. None of these options aligned with their carefully planned strategy for smart homeownership and wealth building.</p><p>Experiencing similar rejection?<a href="https://stairwaymortgage.com/schedule-call/"> Schedule a call</a> to discuss alternative qualification methods.</p><h2><b>The Discovery: Learning About Fannie Mae HomeStyle Renovation Loan Programs</b></h2><h3><b>How Did Amanda Discover HomeStyle Renovation Loan Financing?</b></h3><p>Amanda discovered HomeStyle renovation loan programs through a colleague in the design industry who had used one to purchase and renovate her own home several years earlier. The colleague explained how HomeStyle renovation loans are specifically designed by Fannie Mae to help homebuyers purchase properties needing improvements and finance both the purchase and renovation costs in a single loan with a single closing.</p><p>Intrigued by this solution that seemed perfectly suited to her situation, Amanda researched HomeStyle renovation loan programs thoroughly and scheduled a consultation with a loan advisor specializing in renovation financing for primary residences. She brought detailed renovation plans, contractor estimates, before-and-after renderings from her design work, and a comprehensive budget to the meeting.</p><h3><b>What Makes HomeStyle Renovation Loan Programs Different from Traditional Mortgages?</b></h3><p>During the consultation, the loan advisor explained how HomeStyle renovation loan programs offer distinct advantages for homebuyers purchasing properties needing improvements. Unlike traditional mortgages that only finance existing value, HomeStyle renovation loans allow borrowers to finance based on the home's projected after-renovation value—the value the property will have once all planned improvements are complete.</p><p>The lender would provide a single loan covering both the purchase price and renovation costs, then disburse renovation funds through a controlled draw schedule as work progressed and passed inspection. This meant Amanda would close once, have one mortgage with one interest rate, and access all the capital needed for her complete renovation vision—dramatically simpler than managing multiple separate loans.</p><p>"That consultation gave me so much clarity and relief," Amanda said. "For the first time, I saw how we could purchase this house and transform it into our dream home through a single, manageable financing structure. This wasn't just about getting a mortgage—it was about accessing a comprehensive financing solution that matched our needs perfectly and allowed us to build equity immediately through strategic improvements. It finally made sense."</p><h2><b>The Solution: HomeStyle Renovation Loan Approval and Renovation Process</b></h2><h3><b>What Documentation Did Amanda Provide for HomeStyle Renovation Loan Approval?</b></h3><p>Amanda worked with her loan advisor to assemble the required documentation for a HomeStyle renovation loan application. The process required more detailed planning than a standard home purchase because the lender needed to understand both the current property condition and the complete scope of planned renovations.</p><p><b>Documentation provided:</b></p><ul><li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1">Complete employment and income verification for both borrowers</li><li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1">Tax returns demonstrating stable household income</li><li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1">Excellent credit scores with strong payment histories</li><li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1">Bank statements showing appropriate reserves</li><li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1">Standard down payment for primary residence</li><li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1">Detailed renovation budget with line-item costs for all improvements</li><li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1">Multiple contractor bids for major renovation work</li><li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1">Comprehensive scope of work document outlining all planned improvements</li><li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1">Architectural drawings and design plans for kitchen and bathroom renovations</li><li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1">After-renovation value (ARV) estimate based on comparable sales</li><li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1">Professional home inspection report identifying necessary repairs</li><li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1">Renovation timeline with projected completion schedule</li><li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1">Proof of homeowners insurance coverage during renovation period</li><li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1">Contractor licenses, insurance certificates, and references</li></ul><h3><b>How Does the HomeStyle Renovation Loan Draw Schedule Work?</b></h3><p><b>The approval and funding process:</b></p><ol><li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1"><b>Initial consultation</b> – Discussed renovation financing options and project scope</li><li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1"><b>Property selection</b> – Reviewed target property and renovation potential</li><li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1"><b>ARV analysis</b> – Lender evaluated after-renovation value based on comparable sales</li><li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1"><b>Contractor vetting</b> – Reviewed contractor credentials, bids, and timeline</li><li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1"><b>Loan underwriting</b> – Complete financial and property analysis</li><li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1"><b>Appraisal ordered</b> – Property appraised in current condition with as-completed valuation</li><li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1"><b>Conditional approval</b> – Approved pending final documentation</li><li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1"><b>Single closing</b> – Funded purchase price and established renovation reserve account</li><li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1"><b>Initial draw</b> – Released first portion of renovation funds to begin work</li><li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1"><b>Inspection milestones</b> – Lender inspector verified completion at each phase</li><li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1"><b>Subsequent draws</b> – Released additional funds as work progressed and passed inspection</li><li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1"><b>Final inspection</b> – Verified all improvements completed per scope of work</li><li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1"><b>Project completion</b> – Final draw released and renovation complete</li></ol><p>The HomeStyle renovation lender structured Amanda's financing based on the home's projected value after all renovations were complete. The combined purchase price plus renovation costs fell comfortably below the conservative after-renovation appraisal, creating substantial equity immediately upon project completion. The renovation funds were held in a controlled escrow account, with systematic releases tied to inspection milestones—ensuring quality work and protecting both Amanda and the lender throughout the process.</p><p>Ready to purchase?<a href="https://stairwaymortgage.com/purchase-inquiry/"> Submit a purchase inquiry</a> to discuss your scenario.</p><h2><b>The Results: Amanda Transforms Dated House Into Dream Family Home</b></h2><h3><b>What Results Did Amanda Achieve with HomeStyle Renovation Loan Financing?</b></h3><p>Amanda closed on her dream property and began renovations within days. The controlled draw schedule kept the project organized and on track, with funds released systematically as her contractor completed each major phase: kitchen demolition and reconstruction, master bathroom expansion, HVAC replacement, flooring installation throughout, interior and exterior painting, lighting upgrades, and final landscaping touches. The entire project from purchase to move-in took approximately five months.</p><p><b>Final loan outcome:</b></p><ul><li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1">Approved loan amount covered purchase price plus complete renovation scope</li><li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1">Competitive interest rate for primary residence financing</li><li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1">Favorable long-term fixed-rate structure</li><li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1">Single closing simplified the entire process dramatically</li><li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1">Systematic draw schedule ensured efficient project completion</li><li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1">Timeline: Purchase to move-in ready in approximately five months</li><li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1">Property: 3BR/2.5BA ranch home, Charlotte, NC</li><li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1">Substantial equity created through strategic improvements</li><li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1">Modern, functional family home meeting all needs</li></ul><h3><b>How Did HomeStyle Renovation Loan Qualification Compare to Traditional Primary Residence Financing?</b></h3><p><b>Traditional primary residence mortgage:</b></p><ul><li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1">Financed only the purchase price in current dated condition</li><li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1">No renovation capital included in mortgage</li><li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1">Required separate expensive financing for improvements</li><li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1">Amanda's home vision: BLOCKED ✗</li></ul><p><b>HomeStyle renovation loan:</b></p><ul><li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1">Financed both purchase and complete renovation scope in single loan</li><li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1">One closing, one mortgage, one payment</li><li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1">Systematic draw schedule managed renovation efficiently</li><li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1">Amanda's home vision: ACHIEVED ✓</li></ul><h3><b>What Home Value and Family Benefits Did Amanda Create Through Strategic Renovation?</b></h3><p>"Without the HomeStyle renovation loan program, we would have either had to compromise on a different property or lived in a dated house for years before we could afford to renovate," Amanda explained. "Instead, we purchased the home we truly wanted, transformed it into our dream family home exactly as I envisioned, and we moved into a fully renovated house that meets all our needs. The improvements created substantial equity immediately, and we're building wealth through homeownership in the exact property and neighborhood we wanted."</p><p><b>Home transformation results:</b></p><ul><li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1">Purchased property with excellent bones in ideal neighborhood</li><li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1">Completed comprehensive interior and exterior renovations</li><li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1">Created substantial forced equity through strategic improvements</li><li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1">Achieved modern, functional family home perfectly suited to their needs</li><li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1">Home now appraised at value significantly exceeding total investment</li><li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1">Immediate equity position providing foundation for future financial flexibility</li><li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1">Children growing up in stable, beautiful home in excellent school district</li></ul><p>Amanda and her husband view this home as far more than just a place to live—it's the foundation for building generational wealth through smart homeownership. As the home continues appreciating and they pay down the mortgage, they're building equity that could eventually be leveraged for investment properties, college funding, or retirement planning. When the time comes to access that equity for their next wealth-building step, they plan to explore options like a<a href="https://stairwaymortgage.com/loan-programs/heloc/"> HELOC</a> or<a href="https://stairwaymortgage.com/loan-programs/home-equity-loan/"> Home Equity Loan</a>—allowing them to tap into accumulated equity without refinancing and losing the favorable rate they secured on this HomeStyle renovation loan.</p><p>Beyond the financial benefits, Amanda appreciates how the renovation brought her professional expertise and personal homeownership together. She designed every detail herself, managed the project efficiently, and created a home that reflects her family's values and needs perfectly. The experience taught her invaluable lessons about construction management and renovation financing that she now shares with clients facing similar decisions.</p><p>Ready to get started?<a href="https://stairwaymortgage.com/same-day-approval/"> Get approved</a> or<a href="https://stairwaymortgage.com/schedule-call/"> schedule a call</a> to discuss your situation.</p><h2><b>Exploring Other HomeStyle Renovation Loan Options?</b></h2><p>While Amanda used a HomeStyle renovation loan for purchase and renovation, renovation financing works for multiple scenarios:</p><ul><li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1">Already own and want to improve? See how an<a href="https://stairwaymortgage.com/case-studies/homestyle-renovation-loan-refinance/"> investor used HomeStyle renovation loan refinance to upgrade a rental property</a></li><li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1">Investment property renovation? See how a<a href="https://stairwaymortgage.com/case-studies/home-improvement-loan/"> physical therapist used home improvement loan for rental renovation</a></li><li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1"><a href="https://stairwaymortgage.com/case-studies/">View all case studies</a> to find success stories matching your situation</li></ul><h2><b>Key Takeaways for Homebuyers Purchasing Fixer-Upper Properties</b></h2><ul><li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1"><b>HomeStyle renovation loans finance purchase plus improvements in a single loan with one closing</b>—dramatically simpler than managing multiple separate loans and allowing homebuyers to move into fully renovated homes immediately (<a href="https://www.fanniemae.com/">Fannie Mae HomeStyle program details</a>)</li><li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1"><b>After-renovation value determines maximum loan amounts</b>—lenders evaluate what the property will be worth after improvements are complete, allowing buyers to purchase below-market properties and force appreciation through strategic renovations</li><li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1"><b>Comprehensive improvement options are allowed</b>—HomeStyle renovation loans can finance everything from cosmetic updates to major structural changes, room additions, energy efficiency upgrades, and accessibility modifications (<a href="https://www.fanniemae.com/">Fannie Mae eligible improvement guidelines</a>)</li><li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1"><b>Single-close convenience provides significant advantages</b>—one closing means one set of fees, one interest rate, one monthly payment, and dramatically simplified paperwork compared to managing separate purchase and construction loans</li><li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1"><b>Think beyond immediate housing needs</b>—smart homeowners view renovation financing as a wealth-building tool that allows them to purchase properties below market value, add strategic improvements that create instant equity, and build long-term family wealth through homeownership in exactly the property and neighborhood they desire</li></ul><p>Have questions about renovation financing for your home purchase?<a href="https://stairwaymortgage.com/schedule-call/"> Schedule a call</a> with a loan advisor today.</p><h2><b>Alternative Loan Programs for Home Renovation</b></h2><p>If a HomeStyle renovation loan isn't the perfect fit, consider these alternatives:</p><ul><li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1"><a href="https://stairwaymortgage.com/loan-programs/fha-203k-loan/">FHA 203(k) Loan</a> – Government-backed renovation financing with flexible down payment requirements</li><li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1"><a href="https://stairwaymortgage.com/loan-programs/home-improvement-loan/">Home Improvement Loan</a> – Purchase and renovation financing for investment properties</li><li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1"><a href="https://stairwaymortgage.com/loan-programs/construction-loan/">Construction Loan</a> – Financing for ground-up construction or extensive renovations</li><li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1"><a href="https://stairwaymortgage.com/loan-programs/heloc/">HELOC</a> – Access equity from current home for renovation capital</li><li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1"><a href="https://stairwaymortgage.com/loan-programs/cash-out-refinance">Cash-Out Refinance</a> – Refinance and access equity for home improvements</li></ul><p><a href="https://stairwaymortgage.com/loan-programs/">Explore all loan programs</a> to find your best option.</p><h2><b>Helpful HomeStyle Renovation Loan Resources</b></h2><p><b>Learn more about this loan program:</b></p><ul><li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1"><a href="https://stairwaymortgage.com/loan-programs/homestyle-renovation-loan/">Complete HomeStyle Renovation Loan Guide</a> - Detailed requirements, rates, and qualification guidelines</li><li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1"><a href="https://stairwaymortgage.com/loan-calculator/homestyle-ren